                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363 Standard Oil/30: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Persia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Teheran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-09-04T22:00:00+03:25">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 4, 1921—10 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received September 7—10:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>52. British Minister tells me confidentially that his Government has instructed
                    him to protest against Russian oil concessions being transferred to American
                    concern.</p>
                <p>I am also informed that French interests are seeking the same concessions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
